data.database_description: The database is designed to manage an educational platform focused on courses, their authors/tutors, subjects, and student interactions with these components. It consists of tables for course authors/tutors, students, subjects, courses, student course enrolments, and student tests taken. The relationships between tables are established through foreign keys, linking courses to their respective authors/tutors and subjects, and connecting students to the courses they enroll in as well as tracking their test results. This structure facilitates comprehensive management of educational content delivery, authorship, student enrollment, and assessment within an academic environment.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each author or tutor.
Indicator of whether the individual is an author (A), tutor (T), or both (B).
Username for logging into the educational platform.
Hashed password for secure access to the platform.
First name of the author or tutor.
Middle name of the author or tutor, if applicable.
Last name of the author or tutor.
Gender identifier where 'm' stands for male and 'f' stands for female.
Primary address line of the author or tutor's residence.
